Some upstream tarballs ship files with read-only modes (e.g. 0o555).
Real yarn 4 normalises permissions so the owner always has write
(0o755), and the cache zip integrity recorded in yarn.lock is computed
against that normalised form. Without this fix, yarn-berry-fetcher
reproduces the source mode verbatim and produces zips that fail
integrity validation for any package that lacks owner-write in its tar
headers (e.g. @formatjs/intl-utils@3.8.4).

--- a/src/zip.rs
+++ b/src/zip.rs
@@ -137,6 +137,7 @@
                         },
                         Some(
                             mode as u16 & 0o755
+                                | 0o200
                                 | (if (mode & 0o111) != 0 { 0o111 } else { 0 })
                                 | (if (mode & 0o444) != 0 { 0o444 } else { 0 }),
                         ),
